07:12.134 --> 07:19.014
The first time Boko Haram raped me...

07:21.514 --> 07:23.360
...I wanted to die.

07:25.724 --> 07:28.383
I wanted to die.

07:28.384 --> 07:31.651
But then you told me

07:31.654 --> 07:33.694
I had to be strong for the girls.

07:35.804 --> 07:37.514
And so I was.

07:39.764 --> 07:41.922
Now you have to be strong for them.

07:43.384 --> 07:47.093
I don't care what that man says.

07:47.094 --> 07:50.723
I know one thing for sure about you.

07:50.724 --> 07:54.054
You will do anything to save us.

08:10.294 --> 08:13.223
If we don't get a handle on
these professional assassins,

08:13.224 --> 08:15.723
we're going to be hearing
about a lot more war crimes.

08:15.724 --> 08:18.093
Look, this Taggart guy was coerced.

08:18.094 --> 08:21.553
Even if he wasn't, he shot
a terrorist and a traitor.

08:21.554 --> 08:23.553
I'm sick of our soldiers being vilified

08:23.554 --> 08:26.884
for doing what it takes
to protect America.

08:34.304 --> 08:35.592
That is a good idea.

08:35.594 --> 08:36.883
Yeah, it is.

08:36.884 --> 08:38.133
A bit of a sweet tooth myself.

08:38.134 --> 08:39.592
Yeah. Me too.

08:39.594 --> 08:41.763
Yeah, well, there you go.

08:41.764 --> 08:43.383
So, hopefully...

08:43.384 --> 08:45.053
Hey.

08:45.054 --> 08:46.256
Joseph.

08:46.259 --> 08:48.223
Um, I asked Pastor
Adams over for a chat.

08:48.224 --> 08:49.223
Hi, Pastor. Good to see you.

08:49.224 --> 08:50.717
- Hello, Joe.
- Good to see you.

08:50.720 --> 08:52.513
Your wife made some
lovely coffee cake for us.

08:52.514 --> 08:53.673
Actually, it's store-bought.

08:53.674 --> 08:55.593
Oh, well, pardon me.

08:55.594 --> 08:58.053
You know, my cousin is a Ranger.

08:58.054 --> 08:59.383
Oh.

08:59.384 --> 09:01.513
Did I tell you that?

09:01.514 --> 09:04.263
No. No, I don't think you did.

09:04.264 --> 09:08.513
Four tours. Iraq, Afghanistan.

09:08.514 --> 09:09.883
He lost a lot of buddies.

09:09.884 --> 09:12.173
Well, that's tough. I feel for him.

09:12.174 --> 09:15.553
It can be a heavy burden,

09:15.554 --> 09:17.053
even when the cause is just.

09:17.054 --> 09:19.173
And it is just.

09:19.174 --> 09:21.633
What helped, what really grounded him

09:21.634 --> 09:23.673
was coming into the church.

09:23.674 --> 09:27.463
Not just the prayer, but
being with people, Joe.

09:27.464 --> 09:29.269
- Picnics, socials.
- Yeah.

09:29.272 --> 09:31.845
- You can't isolate yourself...
- Look, Pastor, I don't know what...

09:31.847 --> 09:36.053
What you've been told, but, uh...

09:36.054 --> 09:37.763
I'm fine.

09:37.764 --> 09:39.303
I'm fine.

09:39.304 --> 09:41.228
I'm... I'm glad to hear that, Joe.

09:41.231 --> 09:43.053
But we're the ones who
have asked you to do

09:43.054 --> 09:45.343
what must be done for your country.

09:45.344 --> 09:46.963
Let us help you.

09:46.964 --> 09:48.803
Pray with me, Joe.

09:48.804 --> 09:50.264
Okay.

09:53.884 --> 09:57.553
Jesus, we ask you in
the name of the Lord

09:57.554 --> 10:00.963
to bring peace to this
member of your flock.

10:00.964 --> 10:03.923
For you are the eternal shepherd.

10:03.924 --> 10:07.174
You bring us all under
your protective...

10:14.344 --> 10:16.173
I didn't know you were leaving.

10:16.174 --> 10:17.303
I could've helped.

10:17.304 --> 10:18.963
The Viking warrior

10:18.964 --> 10:21.383
looking after the widow
of his fallen comrade?

10:21.384 --> 10:23.514
It's an ancient tradition, right?

10:28.884 --> 10:32.803
You know, I never cheated on him.

10:32.804 --> 10:35.806
I know you all thought
I did... All y'all...

10:35.809 --> 10:37.439
But I never did.

10:40.094 --> 10:41.963
Not until he was dead.

10:41.964 --> 10:43.903
I'll take the blame for it, if you want.

10:43.906 --> 10:45.695
I'm... I'm sorry.

10:45.698 --> 10:47.884
It's... Look, it's not your fault.

10:49.634 --> 10:52.423
I just wish I were you.

10:52.424 --> 10:54.883
You are the lucky one.

10:54.884 --> 10:56.463
Why?

10:56.464 --> 10:59.304
Because you have nothing to lose.

11:09.974 --> 11:13.763
Judge Martinez and her
husband came to dinner.

11:13.764 --> 11:15.343
They asked after you.

11:15.344 --> 11:17.419
She said she'd love to
have you clerk for her.

11:17.422 --> 11:19.383
You were only a semester
away from your J.D.

11:19.384 --> 11:20.673
You could finish up.

11:20.674 --> 11:22.803
We've already talked about this.

11:22.804 --> 11:24.673
I'm not going back to law school.

11:24.674 --> 11:26.963
Did you know this SEAL?

11:26.964 --> 11:28.804
The one that confessed?

11:30.634 --> 11:31.554
No.

11:34.172 --> 11:36.723
I just hate to see you get
caught up in all of this.

11:36.724 --> 11:40.053
Look, what I'm doing
is just as righteous

11:40.054 --> 11:41.423
as your march at Selma.

11:41.424 --> 11:44.463
Son, that was the Civil Rights movement.

11:44.464 --> 11:45.745
There's no comparison.

11:45.748 --> 11:47.963
All right. Tell you
about a buddy of mine.

11:47.964 --> 11:49.843
Good ol' country boy.

11:49.844 --> 11:53.883
He died in my arms a week ago.

11:53.884 --> 11:56.803
And then I took out a guy trying
to save some kidnapped girls

11:56.804 --> 11:58.284
who only wanted to learn how to read.

12:00.514 --> 12:02.723
I killed someone.

12:02.724 --> 12:04.804
And I will do it again.

12:11.884 --> 12:13.963
Is there something you
want to talk about, son?

12:13.964 --> 12:15.634
You ever have any doubts?

12:17.634 --> 12:20.263
Hmm? During the movement.

12:20.264 --> 12:23.553
That what you were doing was right?

12:23.554 --> 12:25.763
Doubts... sure.

12:25.764 --> 12:27.923
There were some dark moments.

12:27.924 --> 12:31.053
Regrets? No.

12:31.054 --> 12:34.343
If I allowed injustice to
happen, then it was on me.

12:34.344 --> 12:36.513
I couldn't stand by and do nothing

12:36.514 --> 12:40.013
We were warriors, too, in our way.

12:40.014 --> 12:43.415
I would've died for
them... and they for me.

12:44.735 --> 12:48.423
Your roommate from Harvard,
uh, Charles Billington,

12:48.424 --> 12:50.923
he's still at the
embassy in Kabul, right?

12:50.924 --> 12:51.923
Yes.

12:51.924 --> 12:53.963
Good.

12:53.964 --> 12:56.463
'Cause I need a favor.

12:56.464 --> 12:59.013
The target is Nilofar Kazbekov...

12:59.014 --> 13:00.762
A Chechen rebel.

13:00.765 --> 13:03.763
Her husband was the dead Chechen
you brought back from Nigeria.

13:03.764 --> 13:06.673
He's a key lieutenant
of Akmal Barayev...

13:06.674 --> 13:08.673
Nilofar's brother, who
may have been leading

13:08.674 --> 13:11.173
the group that snatched
Rip from Boko Haram.

13:11.174 --> 13:12.763
Agency sources tell us

13:12.764 --> 13:16.173
Akmal here stays in close
touch with his sister.

13:16.174 --> 13:18.223
So we need to get her to get him.

13:18.224 --> 13:20.133
She lives in a villa in Panama

13:20.134 --> 13:23.633
paid for by charities
tied to terrorist groups.

13:23.634 --> 13:26.463
We estimate a three-to
five-man security detail.

13:26.464 --> 13:29.673
Going in low-vis, with
non-attributable gear.

13:29.674 --> 13:31.343
On Wednesday nights,

13:31.344 --> 13:34.133
the nanny usually takes
the daughter to the movies.

13:34.134 --> 13:37.264
That's when we'll grab the
target... when she's alone.

